 Router

---

 1️⃣ Layman Meaning

 A router is like a gateway connecting your internal network to the Internet or another network.
 It decides where data should go outside your local network.

Simple Examples:

 Home Wi-Fi router → connects your home devices to Internet
 Office router → connects office LAN to ISP (Internet Service Provider)

---

 2️⃣ IT / Technical Meaning

 Connects one network to another network (LAN ↔ LAN or LAN ↔ Internet)
 Routes traffic based on IP addresses (Layer 3 device)
 Provides Internet access to internal networks
 Can implement routing policies, NAT, VPN

---

 3️⃣ Practical Examples in IT

 Office LAN → Internet
 Branch office → Head office (via VPN or WAN)
 Routing between multiple subnets inside an enterprise network

---

 4️⃣ Simple ASCII Diagram

```
          Internet
              |
          +-------+
          |Router |
          +-------+
        /    |    \
     LAN1   LAN2  LAN3
```

 LAN1, LAN2, LAN3 → internal networks/subnets
 Router directs traffic between them and to Internet



Router = Gateway → connects networks, provides internet, routes traffic by IP.


